After filtering duplicates, irrelevant URLs like social media handles, and video-content websites, we obtained a total of {{arxiv_2111_13611_FO0044||FO}} documents for {{arxiv_2111_13611_FO0045||FO}} entities. Table (ref) provides an overview of the DoCo dataset. We can see that DoCo's labels are imbalanced, as only {{arxiv_2111_13611_FO0046||FO}} of the documents are informative and {{arxiv_2111_13611_FO0047||FO}} are uninformative. The count of documents with non-zero RE tuples is higher than those with non-zero coverage since the RE tuples were not always related to the subject entity, hence irrelevant towards coverage calculation.